They no longer presided in the national councils they no longer executed the resolutions of peace or war . 
were of little moment and their names served only as the legal date of the year in which they had filled the chair of Marius and of Cicero . 
The title of consul was still the most splendid object of ambition , the noblest reward of virtue and loyalty . 
