Zeno enacted that all governors should remain in the province , to answer any accusations , fifty days after the expiration of their power . 
All the civil magistrates were drawn from the profession of the law . 
Some of them procured admittance into families for the purpose of fomenting differences , of encouraging suits , and of preparing a harvest of gain for themselves or their brethren . 
The splendid and popular class was composed of the advocates , who filled the Forum with the sound of their turgid and loquacious rhetoric . 
As in a former period I have traced the civil and military promotion of Pertinax , I shall here insert the civil honors of Mallius Theodorus . 
He was distinguished by his eloquence , while he pleaded as an advocate in the court of the Praetorian praefect . 
He governed one of the provinces of Africa , either as president or consular , and deserved , by his administration , the honor of a brass statue . 
He was appointed vicar , or vice praefect , of Macedonia . 
