The perpetual intercourse between the court and the provinces was facilitated by the construction of roads and the institution of posts . 
But these beneficial establishments were accidentally connected with a pernicious and intolerable abuse . 
The ordinary administration was conducted by those methods which extreme necessity can alone palliate and the defects of evidence were diligently supplied by the use of torture . 
