The name and use of the indictions , which serve to ascertain the chronology of the middle ages , were derived from the regular practice of the Roman tributes . 
Whatever was honorable or important in the administration of the revenue , was committed to the wisdom of the praefects , and their provincia . 
was the object of ordinary taxation and every new purchaser contracted the obligations of the former proprietor . 
A large portion of the tribute was paid in money and of the current coin of the empire , gold alone could be legally accepted . 
The remainder of the taxes , according to the proportions determined by the annual indiction , was furnished in a manner still more direct , and still more oppressive . 
