This accession of territory might be justified by very specious reasons . 
Chalons and Macon were undoubtedly within the original jurisdiction of the Aedui . 
In the Notitia of Gaul , they are enumerated not as Civitates , but merely as Castra . 
They do not appear to have been episcopal seats before the fifth and sixth centuries . 
