describes Vetranio with more temper , and probably with more truth , than either of the two Victors . 
Vetranio was born of obscure parents in the wildest parts of Maesia and so much had his education been neglected , that , after his elevation , he studied the alphabet . 
The doubtful , fluctuating conduct of Vetranio is described by Julian in his first oration , and accurately explained by Spanheim , who discusses the situation and behavior of Constantina . 
The intelligence of these important events , which so deeply affected the honor and safety of the Imperial house , recalled the arms of Constantius from the inglorious prosecution of the Persian war . 
On his arrival at Heraclea in Thrace , the emperor gave audience to the ambassadors of Magnentius and Vetranio . 
These deputies were instructed to soothe the resentment , and to alarm the fears , of Constantius . 
