M In the present text of Ammianus , we read Asper , quidem , sed ad lenitatem propensior which forms a sentence of contradictory nonsense . 
With the aid of an old manuscript , Valesius has rectified the first of these corruptions , and we perceive a ray of light in the substitution of the word vafer . 
If we venture to change lenitatem into lexitatem , this alteration of a single letter will render the whole passage clear and consistent . 
