Immediately after Julian had received the purple at Milan , he was sent into Gaul with a feeble retinue of three hundred and sixty soldiers . 
In his march from Autun , through the heart of the Gallic provinces , Julian embraced with ardor the earliest opportunity of signalizing his courage . 
Before the inevitable disorder could be remedied , two legions were destroyed and Julian was taught by experience that caution and vigilance are the most important lessons of the art of war . 
