They employed three days , and as many nights , in transporting over the Rhine their military powers . 
The trumpets sounded , the military shout was heard through the field , and the two armies rushed with equal fury to the charge . 
The Caesar , who conducted in person his right wing , depended on the dexterity of his archers , and the weight of his cuirassiers . 
The conflict between the two lines of infantry was obstinate and bloody . 
Six thousand of the Alemanni were slain in the field , without including those who were drowned in the Rhine , or transfixed with darts while they attempted to swim across the river . 
Chnodomar himself was surrounded and taken prisoner , with three of his brave companions , who had devoted themselves to follow in life or death the fate of their chieftain . 
Chnodomar experienced an honorable treatment but the impatient Barbarian could not long survive his defeat , his confinement , and his exile . 
