The river bathed the foot of the walls and the town was accessible only by two wooden bridges . 
The severity of the climate was tempered by the neighborhood of the ocean and with some precautions , which experience had taught , the vine and fig tree were successfully cultivated . 
The licentiousness and corruption of Antioch recalled to the memory of Julian the severe and simple manners of his beloved Lutetia where the amusements of the theatre were unknown or despised . 
He indignantly contrasted the effeminate Syrians with the brave and honest simplicity of the Gauls , and almost forgave the intemperance , which was the only stain of the Celtic character . 
