The religions of antiquity , which established a separate order of priests , dedicated a holy race , a tribe or family , to the perpetual service of the gods . 
Such institutions were founded for possession , rather than conquest . 
But the Christian sanctuary was open to every ambitious candidate , who aspired to its heavenly promises or temporal possessions . 
