The municipal offices were of two kinds the one attached to the individual in his character of inhabitant , the other in that of proprietor . 
Constantine had exempted ecclesiastics from offices of the first description . 
The rich , to obtain this privilege , obtained subordinate situations among the clergy . 
He also enacted that ecclesiastics , who wished to be exempt from offices which they were bound to discharge as proprietors , should be obliged to give up their property to their relations . 
