has clearly ascertained , that the theological works of Philo were composed before the death , and most probably before the birth , of Christ . 
In such a time of darkness , the knowledge of Philo is more astonishing than his errors . 
Mens agitat molem , et magno se corpore miscet . 
in Amelius , Porphyry , Plotinus , and , as he thinks , in Plato himself , a superior , spiritual upercosmian soul of the universe . 
But this double soul is exploded by Brucker , Basnage , and Le Clerc , as an idle fancy of the latter Platonists . 
This notion , till it was abused by the Arians , was freely adopted in the Christian theology . 
