An eager spirit of curiosity urged them to explore the secrets of the abyss and the pride of the professors , and of their disciples , was satisfied with the sciences of words . 
In every step of the inquiry , we are compelled to feel and acknowledge the immeasurable disproportion between the size of the object and the capacity of the human mind . 
We may strive to abstract the notions of time , of space , and of matter , which so closely adhere to all the perceptions of our experimental knowledge . 
