The negotiations of peace were accompanied and supported by the most vigorous preparations for war . 
The army , which Julian held in readiness for immediate action , was recruited and augmented by the disorders of the times . 
The cruel persecutions of the faction of Magnentius had filled Gaul with numerous bands of outlaws and robbers . 
A strange disorder , since it continued above seven years . 
