Philosophy had instructed Julian to compare the advantages of action and retirement but the elevation of his birth , and the accidents of his life , never allowed him the freedom of choice . 
The throne of Julian , which the death of Constantius fixed on an independent basis , was the seat of reason , of virtue , and perhaps of vanity . 
left his mind and body always free and active , for the various and important business of an author , a pontiff , a magistrate , a general , and a prince . 
has expressed these philosophical ideas with much eloquence and some affectation , in a very elaborate epistle to Themistius . 
