The office of president was exercised by the venerable praefect of the East , a second Sallust , whose virtues conciliated the esteem of Greek sophists , and of Christian bishops . 
He was assisted by the eloquent Mamertinus , one of the consuls elect , whose merit is loudly celebrated by the doubtful evidence of his own applause . 
But the civil wisdom of two magistrates was overbalanced by the ferocious violence of four generals , Nevitta , Agilo , Jovinus , and Arbetio . 
