The summons of his colleague Florentius was probably delayed till the commencement of the ensuing year . 
The merit of Artemius , who demolished temples , and was put to death by an apostate , has tempted the Greek and Latin churches to honor him as a martyr . 
But as ecclesiastical history attests that he was not only a tyrant , but an Arian , it is not altogether easy to justify this indiscreet promotion . 
