The elaborate work , which he composed amidst the preparations of the Persian war , contained the substance of those arguments which he had long revolved in his mind . 
Some fragments have been transcribed and preserved , by his adversary , the vehement Cyril of Alexandria and they exhibit a very singular mixture of wit and learning , of sophistry and fanaticism . 
But in the assiduous prosecution of these theological studies , the emperor of the Romans imbibed the illiberal prejudices and passions of a polemic divine . 
