In the midst of a rocky and barren country , the walls of Jerusalem enclosed the two mountains of Sion and Acra , within an oval figure of about three English miles . 
After the final destruction of the temple by the arms of Titus and Hadrian , a ploughshare was drawn over the consecrated ground , as a sign of perpetual interdiction . 
Sion was deserted and the vacant space of the lower city was filled with the public and private edifices of the Aelian colony , which spread themselves over the adjacent hill of Calvary . 
