The vain and ambitious mind of Julian might aspire to restore the ancient glory of the temple of Jerusalem . 
He was displeased with the spiritual worship of the synagogue but he approved the institutions of Moses , who had not disdained to adopt many of the rites and ceremonies of Egypt . 
These considerations might influence his designs but the prospect of an immediate and important advantage would not suffer the impatient monarch to expect the remote and uncertain event of the Persian war . 
