A just and severe censure has been inflicted on the law which prohibited the Christians from teaching the arts of grammar and rhetoric . 
The motives alleged by the emperor to justify this partial and oppressive measure , might command , during his lifetime , the silence of slaves and the applause of Gatterers . 
has collected the seeming differences of ancients and moderns . 
They may be easily reconciled . 
The Christians were directly forbid to teach , they were indirectly forbid to learn since they would not frequent the schools of the Pagans . 
