have in like manner usurped the honors of the Catholic saints and martyrs . 
The saints of Cappadocia , Basil , and the Gregories , were ignorant of their holy companion . 
Pope Gelasius , the first Catholic who acknowledges St . 
George , places him among the martyrs qui Deo magis quam hominibus noti sunt . 
He rejects his Acts as the composition of heretics . 
Some , perhaps , not the oldest , of the spurious Acts , are still extant and , through a cloud of fiction , we may yet distinguish the combat which St . 
George of Cappadocia sustained , in the presence of Queen Alexandria , against the magician Afhanasius . 
This transformation is not given as absolutely certain , but as extremely probable . 
