The warmth of the climate disposed the natives to the most intemperate enjoyment of tranquillity and opulence and the lively licentiousness of the Greeks was blended with the hereditary softness of the Syrians . 
Fashion was the only law , pleasure the only pursuit , and the splendor of dress and furniture was the only distinction of the citizens of Antioch . 
The Satire of Julian , and the Homilies of St . 
Chrysostom , exhibit the same picture of Antioch . 
