Note This controversy has not slumbered since the days of Gibbon . 
We have strenuous advocates of the Phoenician origin of the Irish , and each of the old theories , with several new ones , maintains its partisans . 
It would require several pages fairly to bring down the dispute to our own days , and perhaps we should be no nearer to any satisfactory theory than Gibbon was . 
