On the banks of the Tanais , the military power of the Huns and the Alani encountered each other with equal valor , but with unequal success . 
The Huns prevailed in the bloody contest the king of the Alani was slain and the remains of the vanquished nation were dispersed by the ordinary alternative of flight or submission . 
A colony of exiles found a secure refuge in the mountains of Caucasus , between the Euxine and the Caspian , where they still preserve their name and their independence . 
