The Imperial mandate was at length received for transporting over the Danube the whole body of the Gothic nation but the execution of this order was a task of labor and difficulty . 
The children of the Goths , those at least of a distinguished rank , were separated from the multitude . 
But the stipulation , the most offensive to the Goths , and the most important to the Romans , was shamefully eluded . 
The absolute refusal of Valens suspended their progress , and discovered the repentance , the suspicions , and the fears , of the Imperial council . 
