Part V. Whatever may have been the just measure of the calamities of Europe , there was reason to fear that the same calamities would soon extend to the peaceful countries of Asia . 
The urgent consideration of the public safety may undoubtedly authorize the violation of every positive law . 
How far that , or any other , consideration may operate to dissolve the natural obligations of humanity and justice , is a doctrine of which I still desire to remain ignorant . 
